Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.070 --> 00:00:08.039
One of the most popular API documentation specifications is OpenAPI,

00:00:08.039 --> 00:00:11.474
formerly known as the swagger specification.

00:00:11.474 --> 00:00:16.890
OpenAPI allows you to describe your API using JSON or YAML.

00:00:16.890 --> 00:00:21.480
YAML is a markup language commonly used for configuration files.

00:00:21.480 --> 00:00:26.144
With OpenAPI, you can describe available endpoints,

00:00:26.144 --> 00:00:30.975
operations with parameters, authentication methods,

00:00:30.975 --> 00:00:34.050
and contact information about your API.

00:00:34.049 --> 00:00:38.239
Swagger is the name associated with some of the most well-known and

00:00:38.240 --> 00:00:42.664
widely used tools for implementing the open API specification.

00:00:42.664 --> 00:00:45.335
Swagger helps you design, build,

00:00:45.335 --> 00:00:48.429
document, and consume REST APIs.

00:00:48.429 --> 00:00:52.774
SpringFox is a swagger integration for the Spring framework.

00:00:52.774 --> 00:00:55.549
There are several parts to swagger.

00:00:55.549 --> 00:01:01.189
The Swagger Editor; it's a browser-based editor where you can write OpenAPI specs.

00:01:01.189 --> 00:01:07.939
Swagger UI, this renders OpenAPI specs as interactive API documentation.

00:01:07.939 --> 00:01:15.539
Swagger Codegen; it generate server steps in client libraries from an OpenAPI spec.

